Teams is the user interface (and by the way, it=E2=80=99s worth noting that=
 Microsoft also demonstrated explicit Teams app development), the web is th=
e I/O layer, Fluid is the API, and the Microsoft Graph is the data layer. A=
ctual operating systems like Windows, Mac, iOS, and Android are basically O=
EMs.

What was striking to me about Microsoft=E2=80=99s announcement of Copilot W=
ave 2 ( https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-365/blog/2024/09/16/micro=
soft-365-copilot-wave-2-pages-python-in-excel-and-agents/ ) , is how this s=
trategy has been seamlessly adapted for AI. CEO Satya Nadella said in the p=
re-recorded video announcing Wave 2 ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DGz0=
jPfCuvsM ) :

( https://videopress.com/embed/i6oYpXss?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
=3D0&permalink=3D1&muted=3D0&controls=3D1&playsinline=3D0&useAverageColor=
=3D0&preloadContent=3Dmetadata )

You can think of Copilot as the UI for AI. It helps you break down these si=
loes between your work artifacts, your communications, and your business pr=
ocesses. And we=E2=80=99re just getting started. In fact, with scaling laws=
, as AI becomes more capable and even agentic, the models themselves become=
 more of a commodity, and all the value gets created by you how steer, grou=
nd, fine-tune these models with your business data and workflow. And how it=
 composes with the UI layer of human to AI to human interaction becomes cri=
tical.

Today we=E2=80=99re announcing Wave 2 of Microsoft 365 Copilot. You=E2=80=
=99ll see us evolve Copilot in three major ways: first, it=E2=80=99s about =
bringing the web plus work plus pages together as the new AI system for kno=
wledge work. With Pages we=E2=80=99ll show you how Copilot can take any inf=
ormation from the web or your work and turn it into a multiplayer AI-powere=
d canvas. You can ideate with AI and collaborate with other people. It=E2=
=80=99s just magical. Just like the PC birthed office productivity tools as=
 we know them today, and the web makes those canvases collaborative, every =
platform shift has changed work artifacts in fundamental ways, and Pages is=
 the first new artifact for the AI age.

Here is another video explaining the idea behind Pages:

( https://videopress.com/embed/3WblBswB?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
=3D0&permalink=3D1&muted=3D0&controls=3D1&playsinline=3D0&useAverageColor=
=3D0&preloadContent=3Dmetadata )

To get their work done, users need to integrate different kinds of data fro=
m different sources; data-rich content is hard to share across applications=
 and across platforms. New functionality is hard to integrate. Users must f=
ocus on their tools, not their work.

Oh, oops, that=E2=80=99s from the OpenDoc Technology Intro ( https://youtu.=
be/oFJdjk2rq4E?si=3DBCQL6Vi4VijYy2Aq&t=3D54 ) , which continues:

( https://videopress.com/embed/1EmI5wtg?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
