We will show you how you can extend Copilot with agents. Copilot is becomin=
g this new enterprise orchestration layer. Yesterday=E2=80=99s bespoke inte=
ractions with siloed business applications will just simply become Copilot =
agents.

And back to OpenDoc:

( https://videopress.com/embed/rMYQSJxA?hd=3D1&cover=3D1&loop=3D0&autoPlay=
=3D0&permalink=3D1&muted=3D0&controls=3D1&playsinline=3D0&useAverageColor=
=3D0&preloadContent=3Dmetadata )

OpenDoc is based on the concept of component software. Components are small=
, self-contained reusable modules that can be easily assembled into a seaml=
ess solution. Whether you=E2=80=99re a commercial developer, an in-house de=
veloper, or a custom solution builder, component software will provide the =
solution for delivering the most flexible solutions at the lowest costs.

Time will tell if Pages and Agents =E2=80=94 components, really =E2=80=94 f=
are better than OpenDoc; what was notable is that I skipped over the second=
 of the three ways Nadella said that Microsoft was evolving Copilot. That s=
ection was all about applications, including using AI to manage your Outloo=
k inbox, leverage Python in Excel, and build decks in PowerPoint. Those use=
 cases are a lot less forward-looking; they=E2=80=99re also a lot more like=
ly to gain traction, at least in the short term, given they fit into how pe=
ople already work. Meanwhile, the weight of the dream of the unified worksp=
ace has now been transferred to AI; there=E2=80=99s a good chance Copilot P=
ages are much more viable than past efforts, but there is still the matter =
of getting workers to actually use them.

